## Tech Stack

- Static HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript unless a framework is specifically needed
- No external CSS frameworks (no Bootstrap, no Tailwind) — write custom CSS following the design system above
- If a project needs a framework, prefer React with plain CSS or CSS modules
- Every project MUST include a `.gitlab-ci.yml` for GitLab Pages deployment:

```yaml
pages:
  stage: deploy
  script:
    - mkdir -p public
    - cp -r * public/ 2>/dev/null || true
  artifacts:
    paths:
      - public
  only:
    - main
```

---

## Code Style

- Use clean, readable code — we are Solutions Engineers, not developers
- Add comments explaining non-obvious logic
- Keep files organized: separate HTML, CSS, and JS files when possible
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Prefer simplicity over cleverness

---

## Important Notes

- These tools are internal — prioritize functionality and clarity over polish
- Every tool should have a sidebar navigation matching the JW Dashboard pattern if it has multiple views
- Single-view tools can skip the sidebar but should keep the same header, typography, and color palette
- Always include a page title in the top header area
- When in doubt, refer to the JW Platform Dashboard for visual guidance
